---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Hot Water Berwick | Gas, Heat-Pump, Solar, Same-Day Repairs | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Hot water specialists in Berwick — same-day repairs, gas / heat-pump / solar / electric replacements. Solar Vic rebate handled. VBA-licensed. Servicing 3806, Berwick Springs, Timbarra, Eden Rise, Berwick Waters."
  canonical="https://sehotwater.com.au/berwick/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Berwick 3806 &middot; Eden Rise &middot; Berwick Waters &middot; Timbarra</span>
      <h1>Hot water in <span class="accent">Berwick</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Berwick is our home suburb. Same-day repairs anywhere in 3806 &mdash;
        usually on site within 2 hours. Replacements within 1&ndash;3 days. The
        $1,000 Solar Victoria heat-pump rebate handled in-house. VBA-licensed
        plumber, gasfitter and electrician on every job.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Berwick</span>
      <h2>The Berwick hot water story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Two distinct housing stocks &mdash; old township vs new estates.</h3>
        <p>
          Old Berwick around the High Street, Manuka Road and the church
          precinct is mostly 1970s&ndash;1990s brick veneer on quarter-acre
          blocks &mdash; gas storage units (170&ndash;250L Rheem Stellar,
          Rinnai HotFlo) externally mounted, many now 15&ndash;25 years old and
          well past replacement. The new Berwick Waters, Eden Rise and Timbarra
          estates from 2005 onward run gas instantaneous (Rinnai Infinity 26,
          Bosch Highflow) on the side wall &mdash; now hitting the 15&ndash;20
          year replacement mark for the oldest streets.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Heat-pump is the default upgrade here.</h3>
        <p>
          Roughly 65% of Berwick replacements we&rsquo;re doing in 2026 are
          gas-or-electric to heat-pump conversions. The $1,000 Solar Vic
          rebate plus STCs drops a 280L heat-pump to $3K&ndash;$4.5K net &mdash;
          on par with a like-for-like gas replacement once you factor running
          cost savings (~$500/year). For 3&ndash;4 person families we default
          to the Reclaim 250L/315L or Sanden 315L. Compressor placement is
          usually next to the existing gas meter or AC condenser, well clear
          of bedroom windows.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">The Rheem Stellar bulge.</h3>
        <p>
          Rheem Stellar storage was the default install in Berwick from
          roughly 1998&ndash;2008. That puts most of them at 18&ndash;28 years
          old now &mdash; well beyond the 10&ndash;12 year cylinder life. We
          replace 3&ndash;5 of these a week. Telltales: rust staining at the
          tundish, water around the base, longer recovery times. Once the
          cylinder leaks, replacement is the only option.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Berwick jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Rheem Stellar 170L gas storage replacement &mdash; like-for-like Rinnai HotFlo or upgrade to Rinnai Infinity 20 instantaneous ($1.9K&ndash;$2.6K)</li>
          <li>Gas storage to heat-pump conversion (Reclaim 250L) &mdash; $3.5K&ndash;$4K net after rebates</li>
          <li>Solar hot water tank replacement (Apricus, Rheem Loline) &mdash; existing roof panels retained ($2.5K&ndash;$3.5K)</li>
          <li>Same-day no-hot-water repair &mdash; pilot light, thermostat, element, valve ($200&ndash;$500)</li>
          <li>Electric 315L to heat-pump 280L conversion &mdash; same circuit, $3K&ndash;$4K net</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other South East service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cranbourne/">Cranbourne</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/narre-warren/">Narre Warren</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/hampton-park/">Hampton Park</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/endeavour-hills/">Endeavour Hills</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/south-east-melbourne/">All South East Melbourne</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Berwick hot water quote.</h2>
        <p>Heat-pump vs gas honest comparison. Solar Vic rebate done in-house.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
